# Algebraic effects + handler + `resume` on every backend

Pins the core algebraic-effects surface across all codegen lanes. Until
2026-07-19 the **v2-JS** backend (`run-js --v2`) crashed on the first `perform`
with `unimplemented primitive: effect.perform.oneshot` — while native and
JVM-bytecode had full parity (`specs/v2-state-2026-07-18.md` §R2). This case
exercises an effect declaration, two `perform`s inside a function, and a
collecting handler that accumulates via `resume`, so a v2-JS regression on the
perform/handle/resume machinery fails the suite (`v2-f6-backends` J3).

Scoped to the one-shot collecting-handler pattern all five lanes agree on
(INT/v1-JS/v1-JVM/v2-JS/v2-JVM). Multi-shot handlers and native effect-runner
plugins (`runState`/`runLogger`) are NOT pinned here: the v1 codegen backends do
not implement them, so they cannot share one expected file.

```scalascript
effect Console:
  def writeLine(s: String): Unit

def program(): Unit =
  Console.writeLine("first")
  Console.writeLine("second")
  Console.writeLine("third")

val lines = handle { program(); List() } {
  case Console.writeLine(msg, resume) => msg :: resume(())
}

println(lines)
```
